00:52:05.760 --> 00:52:07.280
No.

00:52:07.280 --> 00:52:09.770
Another one-- I'm
running out of time here.

00:52:09.770 --> 00:52:11.620
I got to wrap this
up real quick.

00:52:11.620 --> 00:52:13.440
Lump charcoal is better.

00:52:13.440 --> 00:52:14.650
It looks natural.

00:52:14.650 --> 00:52:18.100
It looks like God
gave us this charcoal.

00:52:18.100 --> 00:52:20.380
Briquettes look like somebody
made them in a factory.

00:52:20.380 --> 00:52:21.210
Well, they did.

00:52:21.210 --> 00:52:23.830
But I tell you, the
briquettes are just

00:52:23.830 --> 00:52:25.050
as good, if not better.

00:52:25.050 --> 00:52:27.420
And there's a whole
bunch of reasons.

00:52:27.420 --> 00:52:32.150
And among them is the
process of making charcoal

00:52:32.150 --> 00:52:34.180
means carbonizing the wood.

00:52:34.180 --> 00:52:36.070
And if you don't
carbonize it thoroughly,

00:52:36.070 --> 00:52:39.380
which is a problem when you
make it from lump charcoal,

00:52:39.380 --> 00:52:40.727
it can belch out a lot of smoke.

00:52:40.727 --> 00:52:42.810
And you don't know where
the smoke is coming from,

00:52:42.810 --> 00:52:43.950
what the wood is.

00:52:43.950 --> 00:52:47.360
I want to control the wood
flavor by choosing my own wood.

00:52:47.360 --> 00:52:48.550
Charcoal is for heat.

00:52:48.550 --> 00:52:50.130
Wood is for flavor.

00:52:50.130 --> 00:52:53.630
So I much prefer
briquettes because they're

00:52:53.630 --> 00:52:56.110
known entities of heat.

00:52:56.110 --> 00:52:59.060
I really can't take much more
time to talk about this later.

00:52:59.060 --> 00:53:04.240
And my final myth is
barbecue is for guys.

00:53:04.240 --> 00:53:05.780
There are more and
more women now.

00:53:05.780 --> 00:53:08.590
Our Google Analytics
are telling us

00:53:08.590 --> 00:53:12.872
that we're running
around 75% to 80% male.

00:53:12.872 --> 00:53:14.330
So it's still a
backyard guy thing.

00:53:14.330 --> 00:53:16.710
And I don't know why for sure.

00:53:16.710 --> 00:53:18.170
I know this.

00:53:18.170 --> 00:53:19.840
The anthropologists,
the scientists

00:53:19.840 --> 00:53:25.530
tell us that homo erectus were
the first of our ancestors

00:53:25.530 --> 00:53:26.230
to cook.

00:53:26.230 --> 00:53:29.160
Homo erectus, the
guys were the hunters.

00:53:29.160 --> 00:53:32.660
And the girls were
the pit masters.

00:53:32.660 --> 00:53:35.420
The first women were the pit
masters, or pit mistresses,

00:53:35.420 --> 00:53:36.160
if you will.

00:53:36.160 --> 00:53:42.280
How they ceded the control over
fire to men, maybe the same way

00:53:42.280 --> 00:53:44.790
they lost control over
the remote control.

00:53:44.790 --> 00:53:46.582
I don't know how this happened.

00:53:46.582 --> 00:53:48.540
I do know that we're
seeing more and more women

00:53:48.540 --> 00:53:50.130
cooking outdoors.

00:53:50.130 --> 00:53:53.130
I think part of it
is that women just

00:53:53.130 --> 00:53:55.310
want guys to have their fun.

00:53:55.310 --> 00:53:56.220
Have their space.

00:53:56.220 --> 00:54:00.350
Let them think they're
doing something useful,

00:54:00.350 --> 00:54:02.250
that they're actually cooking.

00:54:02.250 --> 00:54:04.320
They're contributing
to the family welfare.

00:54:04.320 --> 00:54:06.708
Sort of like faking
orgasm I think.

00:54:06.708 --> 00:54:09.048
[LAUGHTER]

00:54:09.990 --> 00:54:11.720
But more and more
women are grilling.

00:54:11.720 --> 00:54:13.710
And I say, let them have it.

00:54:13.710 --> 00:54:15.470
That's less work for me.

00:54:15.470 --> 00:54:18.300
All right, well that
covers my-- there

