MEATHEAD GOLDWYN:
Well, we've got two.

00:57:40.190 --> 00:57:41.150
CHRIS: [INAUDIBLE] waiting.

00:57:41.150 --> 00:57:42.432
MEATHEAD GOLDWYN: OK, go ahead.

00:57:42.432 --> 00:57:42.973
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:57:42.973 --> 00:57:44.290
So I'm curious.

00:57:44.290 --> 00:57:48.540
What's a better grill--
Weber, Green Egg, Kenmore?

00:57:48.540 --> 00:57:52.282
Do you have like a
favorite preference?

00:57:52.282 --> 00:57:53.740
MEATHEAD GOLDWYN:
I have favorites.

00:57:53.740 --> 00:57:56.120
I have this guy, Max,
who tests grills.

00:57:56.120 --> 00:57:58.290
And he's the real expert on it.

00:57:58.290 --> 00:58:02.100
Weber is just as good as
gold, always reliable.

00:58:02.100 --> 00:58:05.480
They have inventory parts--
parts inventory going back

00:58:05.480 --> 00:58:06.510
decades.

00:58:06.510 --> 00:58:08.840
Something breaks, they're
there to help you.

00:58:08.840 --> 00:58:10.060
I love their products.

00:58:10.060 --> 00:58:12.050
They're not always
the latest, keenest.

00:58:12.050 --> 00:58:13.740
Some of the coolest
new developments

00:58:13.740 --> 00:58:15.194
are by other manufacturers.

00:58:15.194 --> 00:58:17.360
But I don't think you'll
ever go wrong with a Weber.

00:58:17.360 --> 00:58:19.180
And they all work well.

00:58:19.180 --> 00:58:20.360
Big Green Eggs are nice.

00:58:20.360 --> 00:58:23.010
They're a very different
concept, very different

00:58:23.010 --> 00:58:25.270
thermodynamic properties.

00:58:25.270 --> 00:58:29.450
I think of them as better
smokers than grills.

00:58:29.450 --> 00:58:31.820
They're great pizza ovens.

00:58:31.820 --> 00:58:35.240
They cook really well
in cold climates.

00:58:35.240 --> 00:58:36.570
Not my all time favorite.

00:58:36.570 --> 00:58:40.355
I know Green Egg people
are rabid about them.

00:58:40.355 --> 00:58:41.730
And if there's
one in here, he'll

00:58:41.730 --> 00:58:44.820
probably jump up on the
stage and strangle me.

00:58:44.820 --> 00:58:47.890
But they're not my
all time favorite.

00:58:47.890 --> 00:58:51.120
And Kenmore, I'm
not too familiar

00:58:51.120 --> 00:58:53.930
with the various
models that they make.

00:58:53.930 --> 00:58:54.925
AUDIENCE: Thanks.

00:58:54.925 --> 00:58:55.800
MEATHEAD GOLDWYN: OK.

00:58:55.800 --> 00:58:56.950
Well, thank you very much.

00:58:56.950 --> 00:58:59.290
And if you did buy a book, I'd
be happy to sign it for you.

00:58:59.290 --> 00:59:00.206
CHRIS: That was great.

00:59:00.206 --> 00:59:01.000
Super educational.

00:59:01.000 --> 00:59:01.870
Thank you very much, Meathead.

00:59:01.870 --> 00:59:03.036
MEATHEAD GOLDWYN: Thank you.

